## Multi-Window Development
This window is for **Flutter App** development.
Always start from `dev`. If local `dev` does not exist, create it from `origin/dev` or `origin/main`.
Never implement daily development directly on `main`; `main` is staging/pre-release only.
Production work must come from a GitHub Release / `v*` tag, not from an ad hoc branch.
Always verify Onboarding flow, GEOIP sync, and sing-box config compatibility with Backend and NodeAgent.

## Task Completion Report
When a task or subtask is complete, use the standard completion report from:
@docs/ai-rules/v3.7/16-Task-Completion-Report.md

The report must explicitly say which other repo windows are unlocked for parallel development and which remain blocked.

## DoD Self-Check
- [ ] Linked to TASK-XXXX
- [ ] Onboarding + first connection closed loop verified
- [ ] Cross-repo impact on Backend/NodeAgent checked
- [ ] Local black/white list and encryption considered
